  "texts": [
    "The deep learning component, N, is tasked with primary language processing functions, formalized as:L(x; Θ) = softmax(N (x; Θ))(1)where x represents the input data and Θ denotes the trainable parameters of the neural network.",
    "The softmax function is applied to the output of N to obtain a probabilistic distribution over the language model's vocabulary.To assimilate symbolic reasoning, a rule-based logic layer, R, is meticulously integrated atop N. This layer is defined by a set of rules R = {r 1, r 2,..., r n }, each rule r i being a logical construct that transforms an input state s into an output state s ′ based on the rule's logical framework:s ′ = r i (s), ∀i ∈ {1, 2,..., n}(2)The integration facilitates a bi-directional flow of knowledge.",
    "The symbolic system S is enriched by expert knowledge E and extracts knowledge from the inductive learning system I, mathematically formalized as:S = f (S, E) + K(I, dS)(3)where f (•) represents the knowledge augmentation function, and K denotes the knowledge extraction operation, which is anTABLE I: Selected BIG-bench Tasks for Evaluating TinyLlama BIG-bench Task Relevance to TinyLlama Analogical Reasoning Tests symbolic logic application Word Sense Disambiguation Assesses contextual language understanding Causal Judgment Evaluates understanding of cause-effect relationships Mathematical Reasoning Measures logic in numerical contexts Commonsense Reasoning Challenges with everyday logic and knowledge Natural Language Inference Examines reasoning in language entailment Novel Conceptualization Gauges creativity and conceptual understanding Quantitative Reasoning Assesses ability to handle quantities and measurements Scientific Understanding Evaluates grasp of scientific concepts and terminology Temporal Understanding Tests comprehension of time-based narrativesintegral over the differential changes in the symbolic system S.Conversely, the inductive learning system I, typified by the neural network N, is fed by a corpus of training samples T, and its learning is augmented by a transfer of structured knowledge from S:I = g(I, T) + ∇S(4)Here, g(•) is the inductive learning function, and ∇S represents the gradient of the symbolic system knowledge, indicating the direction and rate of knowledge transfer to the inductive learning system.This bidirectional knowledge dynamic is pivotal, as it ensures that I and S not only operate in tandem but also evolve through mutual interaction.",
    "The complexity of this hybrid model promises to significantly elevate the accuracy of information retrieval and the capacity of TinyLlama to handle multifaceted, logic-intensive queries.",
    "Data Preparation and ProcessingThe data preparation for TinyLlama is an intricate procedure, meticulously curating a dataset that spans an extensive array of texts drawn from books, scholarly articles, websites, and other forms of digital media."
  ],
